[[File:Logo of APBA.png|thumb]]
The '''American Power Boat Association''' ('''APBA''') is an American membership-owned corporation. It was created in 1903 by an act of the New York legislature as a racing association for [[powerboat]]s, and  is based in [[Eastpointe, Michigan]], near Detroit.{{cn|date=January 2018}}  It is the United States sanctioning authority for the [[Union Internationale Motonautique]], the world governing body for powerboat racing. It is the sole governing body in the United States, and sanctions races in a number of different classes.{{cn|date=January 2018}}

== Hall of Champions ==
Each year, the association inducts powerboat drivers into its "Hall of Champions". 
*2009 induction<ref>{{cite web|title=Steve David To Be APBA Hall Of Champions Inductee|publisher=H1 Unlimited|url=http://h1unlimited.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=775&Itemid=59|accessdate=2011-03-05}}</ref>
*2010 induction<ref>{{cite web|title=APBA Hall of Champions banquet |date=January 29, 2011 |publisher=Hydroplane Quebec |url=http://hydroplanequebec.com/en/2011/01/apba-hall-of-champions-banquet/ |accessdate=2011-03-05 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110712233358/http://hydroplanequebec.com/en/2011/01/apba-hall-of-champions-banquet/ |archivedate=2011-07-12 |df= }}</ref>

