[[File:Trask Coliseum.jpg|thumb|Front entrance to Trask Coliseum]] [[File:20081017 Sammy C. Hawk.jpg|thumb|left|[[University of North Carolina at Wilmington|UNCW]] [[mascot]] Sammy C. Hawk celebrates 2008 [[Midnight Madness (basketball)|Midnight Madness]]]] '''Trask Coliseum''' (also known as "The Perch"), is a 5,200-seat multi-purpose [[arena]] in [[Wilmington, North Carolina]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Trask Coliseum|url=http://uncw.edu/BA/campus_map/trask.htm|website=uncw.edu|accessdate=26 April 2015}}</ref>
The coliseum was opened in 1977 and named after Raiford Graham Trask, a trustee of Wilmington College. <ref>{{cite web|last1=Steelman|first1=Ben|title=Who are the Trasks?|url=http://www.myreporter.com/2009/06/the-trasks/|website=www.myreporter.com|accessdate=26 April 2015}}</ref>
It is home to the [[University of North Carolina at Wilmington]] Seahawks [[basketball]] [[team]], as well as some graduations for New Hanover County high schools.
